parameters: Vega

\SE[74]The toxins in the water are stronger than the
deformed terrain.... \!\SE[3]...Just as Vita had told me.
Vega

\SE[67]If we use something like this as drinking water...
the human body...
Gatekeeper Hidari
The collection here is finished.
Vega

\SE[7]Good work. I'm done here too. \SE[2]With this amount,
it's enough as a sample.
Gatekeeper Hidari

Even so... Magic is amazing, isn't it? To think it can
neutralize even such poison....
Vega

\SE[2]What are you talking about? \.Normal magic can't
neutralize this poison.
Gatekeeper Hidari
...Huh?
Vega

\SE[2]But that's right, isn't it? If we can neutralize this
with \SE[3]magic, then we should refine \SE[3]Cordain
ourselves.
Vega

\SE[2]Normal magic is more like a cold medicine. \.So, it's
not enough to nullify this. \!\SE[3]We need a stronger
special medicine.
Gatekeeper Hidari
Was that something Lunaroa-san was using earlier...?
Vega

\SE[76]That person, because they're crazy, they figured out
the answer. \.This is like a special medicine kind of magic.
\!\SE[3]...I can't do the same thing.
Gatekeeper Hidari
The one who can do that is that Lunaroa...
Gatekeeper Hidari

Then, why doesn't Lunaroa-san spread this special medicine?
Even now, there are still damages occurring somewhere...
Vega
\SE[2]Wait, are you seriously asking that?
Gatekeeper Hidari
Huh, is that so...
Vega

\SE[75]You're surprisingly straightforward, aren't you...
\SE[74]Certainly, if we spread this special medicine, we can
greatly reduce the immediate damage.
Vega

\SE[3]Which country will benefit the most from this benefit?
\!\SE\SE[3]Which country will gain the most advantages from
strengthening through refinement? \.\SE[3]I wonder which
country will be able to obtain the most benefits?
Gatekeeper Hidari
Cordain....
Vega

\SE[2]That's right. \!\SE[3]While we can reduce the
immediate damage, \.where do you think the resulting
increased national power will go?
Gatekeeper Hidari
Ulyssean....
Vega

\SE[52]I'm sure you already understand. \SE[3]There are also
spies among the Ulysseans, right? If information leaks from
there, it will lead to even greater damage.
Vega

\SE[74]That's why, even if there are damages, we have to
turn a blind eye. \SE[75]Because that will lead to better
results.
Gatekeeper Hidari
That must be... a difficult situation for you.
Vega

\SE[60]Well, it's the unique pain of those who have.
\SE[3]You could call it the fame tax, I suppose.
Vega
\SE[84]So you also have to keep it a secret, okay?
Gatekeeper Migii

May I ask you something? We have found a large hole deep in
the forest. I would like to hear your opinion from that
perspective, if possible.
Vega
\SE[2]Large hole...?
